Definition: Two analogies that relate places/locations to the associated travel mode is given in the form "A : B. C : ?". "A : B" relates place A to travel mode B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate travel mode for the given place C, following the "A : B" relation.

Positive Examples.explanation: Rockets are used to travel to the moon - hence the given analogy relates places/locations to the associated travel mode , and the answer also does the same
A bus can be used to travel to the mall - hence the given analogy relates places/locations to the associated travel mode , and the answer also does the same
If an airplane can be used to travel to australia - the given analogy relates places/locations to the associated travel mode , and the answer also does the same

Negative Examples.explanation: The given analogy relates places/locations to the associated travel mode , BUT the answer does not model the same
If a taxi can be used to travel to restaurant - rocket is not the right answer for travelling to downtown
If a car can be used to travel to an airport - bicycle is not the right answer for travelling to bermuda
